<item>
            <title>[LU-1579] osd_declare_xattr_set() doesn&apos;t reserve credits for version set</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1579</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the osd_declare_xattr_set() for ldiskfs:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (strcmp(name, XATTR_NAME_VERSION) == 0) {
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* no credits &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; version */&lt;/span&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; 0;
        }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So if a caller calls only dt_version_set() to set inode version, the reserved credits for this transaction will be zero. I think we&apos;d reserve 1 block for version set.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="15073">LU-1579</key>
            <summary>osd_declare_xattr_set() doesn&apos;t reserve credits for version set</summary>
